<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "You recently requested a special enrollment period due to experiencing a qualifying event, #{notice.sep.title}. Upon review of the information you provided on #{TimeKeeper.date_of_record}, your request has been denied. The date you submitted does not qualify you for a special enrollment period.Based on the date you experienced this event, you can only report this event between <strong>#{notice.sep.start_on}</strong> through <strong>#{notice.sep.end_on}</strong>. Qualifying events cannot be reported prior to the date of the event. If you are trying to report a future event, please come back on or after the actual date of the event. If you believe this decision is the result of an error, please contact the #{Settings.site.short_name} Contact Center at #{notice.hbe.phone} [TTY 711] for additional assistance."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "This means that, although you may be eligible to participate in #{Settings.site.short_name}, you are not eligible to enroll in or make changes to your current plan through a special enrollment period. This is because the annual open enrollment period is closed and you reported your qualifying event after #{notice.sep.end_on} or before the qualifying event occurred."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
content: "Please note that your employer’s annual Open Enrollment for Plan Year #{notice.plan_year.open_enrollment_start_on.year} closed on #{notice.plan_year.open_enrollment_end_on}. Open enrollment occurs for a period of time each year when eligible employees can enroll into a plan for the first time, add or drop family members, change their plan, or terminate coverage. Once open enrollment ends each year, employees must meet certain criteria to be able to enroll, terminate, or make other changes to their coverage. This is called a special enrollment period. Circumstances that allow employees to enroll in health plans through a special enrollment period include the following, <u>when reported promptly</u> (usually within 30 days)."} %>

  <table class="total_table" border="0">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <ul>
            <li style="margin-top: 0px;">
              Gaining access to new health plans as a result of a permanent move
              <ul>
                <li>As long as you had previous comprehensive health coverage for at least one day of the 60 days prior to the move, or were moving from a foreign country or a U.S. territory</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Birth, adoption, placement for adoption, or placement for foster care
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Getting married or entering a domestic partnership
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Getting divorced or terminating a domestic partnership
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Death of an employee or dependent
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Loss of minimum essential health coverage resulting from a loss of eligibility due to:
              <ul>
                <li>Termination of employment or change in employment status</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Loss of dependent status due to child aging off a parent’s plan</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>No longer residing, living, or working in the health plan’s service area</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Loss of minimum essential coverage due to:
              <ul>
                <li>Termination of employer contributions</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Exhaustion of COBRA or state continuation coverage</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Loss of pregnancy-related Medicaid coverage</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Loss of medically needy Medicaid coverage</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Any other involuntary loss of coverage</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Losing access to employer-sponsored coverage because employee enrolls in Medicare
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Losing access to COBRA or state continuation coverage because employer failed to submit premiums on time
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Losing eligibility for coverage under a State Medicaid or CHIP program
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Unintentional, inadvertent, or erroneous failure to enroll that was the fault of a <%= Settings.site.short_name %> employee or the enrollment error was the result of error, misrepresentation, misconduct, or inaction by a broker or assister providing enrollment assistance, or an insurance company representative
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              A qualified health plan substantially violates a material provision of its contract
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              An employee or dependent demonstrates that a material error related to plan benefits, service areas, or premium influenced their decision to enroll in a QHP
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Being the victim of domestic abuse or spousal abandonment, or a dependent of the victim
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Losing eligibility for an exemption from the individual mandate penalty outside of an annual open enrollment period
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Starting or concluding service as an AmeriCorps State and Local, NCCC, or VISTA volunteer
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Being a registered member of Native American tribe, or their dependent, under section 4 of the Indian Health Care Improvement Act
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Being court-ordered to obtain health coverage for yourself or someone else
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              Consumer prevented from enrolling during their annual open enrollment or special enrollment period due to:
              <ul>
                <li>Natural disaster such as an earthquake, massive flooding, or hurricane</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Serious medical condition such as an unexpected hospitalization or temporary cognitive disability</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Loss of pregnancy-related Medicaid coverage</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li><%= Settings.site.short_name %> system outage</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

